Giant concrete arrows were placed across the US when the US Postal Service began delivering air mail in 1924 . 
  The New York to San Francisco route was the first land-based navigation system in the world . 
  Retired couple Brian and Charlotte Smith have found 102 of the markers in the US . 
  They were placed at the base of beacons to help pilots find their way . 
  The pair have travelled across the country to photograph the monuments . 
 